<br>
<br>
<br>
<DIV class="poemtitle">the glue makers’ guild </DIV><br>
  <div align="center"><img src="images/gluemakersguild.jpg"><br>
  <a class="artistline" href="javascript:goauthor('jones');">art by Pat Jones</a></div><br>
<TABLE><TR><TD>
<br>
<br>
they labor in sweating cells <br />
in midnight under the city <br />
they glide cowled past each other <br />
<br />
their eyes never meet - each hugs <br />
the stain of his own recipe <br />
to the roiling scars of his body <br />
<br />
no talk in the catacombs <br />
just the stink and boil <br />
of a thousand cauldrons <br />
<br />
the glue makers draw on <br />
under-cloak ingredients <br />
won in appalling ways <br />
for hours they stir and test <br />
and stir again <br />
<br />
when the fire banks itself <br />
when the hot ferment of the pot <br />
stills to a fretful murmur <br />
the glue makers anoint themselves <br />
with care and blazing eyes <br />
<br />
they don borrowed smiles <br />
and move up into the daylight <br />
to hunt with deadly purpose <br />
<br />
the clean of limb <br />
the sound of sleep <br />
the laughing<br />
<br /><br>
<br>

<a class="byline" href="javascript:goauthor('sebastian')">by Nic Sebastian</a><br><br><br>
</TD></TR></TABLE>
</div>
		
